INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '809c93dc-e274-4890-b51f-cd8c3f294087',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Express Middleware — Pipeline Order, Global vs Route-Scoped, and Why Sequence Is Everything$escape$,
  $escape$Express processes every request through a linear middleware stack. Each middleware receives `(req, res, next)` and must either terminate the request or call `next()` to pass control forward — skipping `next()` silently hangs the request.

Global middleware registered with `app.use()` runs for every route. Route-specific middleware is passed directly as arguments before the handler: `app.get('/admin', authGuard, handler)`. Order of `app.use()` calls is the order of execution — register `express.json()` before any route that reads `req.body`, or it arrives undefined.

A critical gotcha: error-handling middleware must have exactly four parameters `(err, req, res, next)`. Express detects the arity and only routes to it when `next(err)` is called. Place it after all routes, or errors from earlier handlers bypass it entirely.

For route groups, `express.Router()` creates an isolated mini-pipeline. Middleware applied to a router instance only affects that router's routes, keeping concerns like auth or rate-limiting scoped without polluting the global stack.$escape$,
  $escape$import express from 'express';

const app = express();
const router = express.Router();

// Global — runs for every request
app.use(express.json());
app.use((req, _res, next) => { console.log(req.method, req.url); next(); });

// Router-scoped auth guard
const authGuard = (req, res, next) =>
  req.headers.authorization ? next() : res.status(401).json({ error: 'Unauthorized' });

router.use(authGuard);
router.get('/profile', (req, res) => res.json({ user: req.user }));

app.use('/api', router);

// Error handler — must be LAST, exactly 4 params
app.use((err, _req, res, _next) => res.status(500).json({ error: err.message }));

app.listen(3000);$escape$,
